Style Description: Cyberpunk Neon Interface

Theme: Dark futuristic cyberpunk with neon accents

Color Palette:
- Background: Dark gray (bg-gray-900)
- Secondary Background: Slightly lighter gray (bg-gray-800)
- Primary Accent: Neon Yellow (text-yellow-400, border-yellow-400)
- Secondary Accent: Neon Blue (text-blue-300)
- Text: Light gray (text-gray-100)
- Input Background: Dark gray (bg-gray-800)

Typography:
- Font Family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif
- Headings: Large, bold, using primary accent color (text-yellow-400)
- Body Text: Light gray (text-gray-100)

Layout:
- Full-height layout with sticky header and footer
- Content centered vertically and horizontally in the main area

Components:
1. Navbar:
   - Background: bg-gray-800
   - Border bottom: border-yellow-400
   - Logo/Title: text-2xl font-bold text-yellow-400 with glitch effect
   - Navigation links: text-blue-300 with hover effect to text-yellow-400

2. Buttons:
   - Background: bg-yellow-400
   - Text: text-black
   - Hover: bg-yellow-300
   - Rounded corners (rounded-md)
   - Transition effects on hover

3. Form Inputs:
   - Border: border-yellow-400
   - Background: bg-gray-800
   - Text and Placeholder: text-gray-100 and placeholder-gray-500
   - Focus: ring-2 ring-yellow-400

4. Glitch Effect:
   - Applied to main headings and logo
   - Uses text-shadow animation for a glitchy, cyberpunk feel

5. Active Navigation Indicator:
   - Neon underline effect using pseudo-element
   - Color: #00fffc with box-shadow for glow effect

Special Effects:
1. Neon Glow: Use box-shadow with the accent colors to create a neon glow effect on borders or text
2. Glitch Animation: Applied to important text elements for a tech-distortion effect
3. Hover Transitions: Smooth color transitions on interactive elements

Responsive Design:
- Use Tailwind's responsive classes to ensure the design works on all screen sizes
- Maintain readability and usability across devices

Footer:
- Background: bg-gray-800
- Border top: border-yellow-400
- Text: text-blue-300

When implementing new pages or components:
1. Stick to the defined color palette
2. Use the Orbitron font for all text
3. Implement glitch effects on main headings
4. Ensure all interactive elements have hover effects
5. Maintain the dark background with neon accents throughout
6. Use centered layouts for main content areas
7. Implement subtle animations or transitions to enhance the futuristic feel
